The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Monday, January 1, 2007

 New Year carnival

 The Telegraph presents Winter Carnival at City Centre, 4.30 pm onwards. Today: Performance by Pipe Band. Followed by a musical evening with DJ Ritesh.

 Festival amp; celebration

 Kalpataru Utsav 2007 at Ramakrishna Math, Cossipore and Dakshineswar Temple, 4 am onwards. 

 Vivekananda Institute of Social Science will observe Kalpataru Divas with a seminar and devotional songs at Abantika Abasan open-air auditorium, Picnic Garden, 6 pm. 

 Eye on art

 Photographs on Calcutta by Arun Ganguly, at Boi-Chitra, College Street Coffee House, 3 pm to 8 pm. 

 Contemporary Perspectives, works by Animesh Nandi, Asit Poddar, Atin Basak, Biswajit Saha, Soumitra Kar, Suman Roy and Tapas Konar, at Gallery Kanishkas, 11 am to 8 pm.

 In A Lyrical Vein, an exhibition of paintings by Ram Lal Dhar, at Anant Art Gallery, 11 am to 7 pm. 

 An exhibition of paintings and sculptures by various artists will open at Charnock City, Salt Lake, 6 pm. 




